<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Reader&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.oprah.com/obc/pastbooks/bernhard_schlink/obc_pb_19990226.jhtml" class="external text" title="http://www.oprah.com/obc/pastbooks/bernhard_schlink/obc_pb_19990226.jhtml" rel="nofollow">Oprah's book club page</a> with biography, reviews, questions and forum</li>
<li><a href="http://www.randomhouse.com/vintage/read/reader/" class="external text" title="http://www.randomhouse.com/vintage/read/reader/" rel="nofollow">Publisher's guide</a> with 16 questions</li>
<li><a href="http://www.bookrags.com/studyguide-reader/" class="external text" title="http://www.bookrags.com/studyguide-reader/" rel="nofollow">bookrags.com study guide</a> with chapter synopses</li>
<li><a href="http://www.Der-Vorleser.com" class="external text" title="http://www.Der-Vorleser.com" rel="nofollow">Der-Vorleser.com</a> Project from a german school class about "The Reader"</li>
<li><a href="http://www.history.ucsb.edu/faculty/marcuse/classes/133c/133cTexts/SchlinkQues042.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.history.ucsb.edu/faculty/marcuse/classes/133c/133cTexts/SchlinkQues042.htm" rel="nofollow">Reading guide with questions</a> from a college German history course</li>
<li><a href="http://culturazzi.org/review/literature/the-reader-bernhard-schlink" class="external text" title="http://culturazzi.org/review/literature/the-reader-bernhard-schlink" rel="nofollow">Book review: The Reader by Bernhard Schlink</a></li>
</ul>


